FBIS3-31882 "dreeu039aa_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS UN's Akashi Meets With Martic, Milosevic Serbs Agree To Withdraw From Bridge LD2502172994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 1611 GMT 25 Feb 94 LD2502172994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Text] Belgrade, 25 February (TANJUG) -- The UN secretary-general's special envoy, Yasushi Akashi, and the president of the Republic of Serb Krajina, Milan Martic, reached an agreement in Belgrade today on the bridge between Gradiska and Stara Gradiska. They agreed that the situation on the bridge is to be restored to what it was on 18 February when the police of the Republic of Serb Krajina took control of the bridge from the UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces]. After one hour of talks, Akashi and Martic said that it was agreed that the UN peace forces are to withdraw armored personnel carriers deployed around the bridge over the past few days and that, at the same time, members of the ministry of internal affairs of the republic of Serb Krajina are to withdraw as well.
